==English==

===Verb===
'''to [[kick]] [[ass]]''' <!-- for inflections, see component terms-->

# {{cattag|slang|idiom}} To be very impressive.
#:''Your new car really '''kicks ass'''!''
# {{cattag|slang|idiom}} To beat someone at something.
#:''You will '''kick his ass''' at tennis!''
# {{cattag|slang|vulgar}} To beat someone at a fight.
#:''You will '''kick his ass'''!''

===Interjection===
'''[[kick]] [[ass]]'''

# {{slang}} Used to express happiness or a feeling of accomplishment.
#:'''''Kick ass'''! I just got to level 47 in World of Warcraft!''

